\f1\b\fs32 GOD
\f0\b0\fs28 \
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}David and his legacy and life - it really was one moment that turned everything\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Everything before 2 Sam 11 is great for David...he is a man after God's own heart, a killer of giants, a leader of men, a lover of God.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Then chapter 11...chapter 11 happens and you probably think you know where I'm going but I'm pretty sure you don't. \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}See David's life ends as a tragedy...a model of what NOT to do when God blesses you.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Explain how David's life ends here\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Trace it backwards - do this in a fun engaging way\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}And it all starts with this one line...it's one of my favorite that I memorized years ago as a reminder..."At the times when kings go off to war, David stayed home".\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I'm pretty sure you probably never noticed that verse before. \
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I call them throw away verses because we tend to skip over them and want to get to the good stuff...David and Bathsheba...that's where the story gets interesting.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}But the whole thing started because of one small alligator...sloth or laziness. And that one alligator destroyed not only his life but the lives of many people.\
\pard\tx560\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \

\f1\b\fs32 YOU
\f0\b0\fs28 \
\pard\tx560\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}And David's story is our story\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I'm willing to bet if you were to look at the greatest compromises or regrets or sins you've had in your life, you can go back far enough to a small compromise. An alligator you thought was cute or not harmful because of it's size...\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}So you thought it about way way before you acted on it\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You fantasized about it\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You invested time and energy into planning it\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You fed it...and it grew...and when a full grown alligator ever gets a hold of you...you've never the same...it always changes you if not kills something important to you.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}So what do you do? DON'T FEED THE ALLIGATORS\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Don't allow small compromises in your life to mess up your life\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Ecc 10:1-2 - a fly...a nuisances...messed it all up.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You may think i've cherry picked the one story that setup my whole premise...but give me some time. Your big issues, struggle, addiction or problem is the result of a very small alligator you fed over time that is now destroying your life.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Next Steps\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Spend some time evaluating your past big mess ups or current ones? What were the small things you did\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Are there any alligators right now you feeding you know are a problem\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li1440\fi-1440\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
